NAYSAYERS RANT: art is not my hobby. Art is the air I breathe. Art is the very thing that moves me. I needed to follow this career path, because IT chose ME. I had no other choice. And I’m SO glad I followed this path. And I’d do it again and again… BUT:

Some people — LOTS of people, in fact — don’t understand. To them, art is in the “hobby category.” It’s not a legitimate field of study, or career path. To this day, I meet people who tell me it’s “CUTE” that I have my own art studio, or that I’ve actually managed to build a “real business” out of this thing. YOU HEARD ME. It’s a hard pill to swallow, and if you’ve pursued any kind of “unconventional path” you can probably relate. I want to shout back, “being myself isn’t CUTE, it’s F*ING AMAZING.” But instead, I usually just say, “thanks.” Well, NOT TODAY. 

TODAY, I want to tell you, loudly and clearly, that the most beautiful and legitimate thing you can do in life is show up as your whole entire self, and use that energy for GOOD. That’s not “cute” — that’s remarkably brave.

SO. To the naysayers, I say 🖕. Because here I am, with a platform of almost 70k AMAZING supporters, and I got here by following MY TRUTH, which I take incredibly seriously. F the “rules” that describe art as a hobby. F any convention that doesn’t honour YOUR truth. That’s my little rant — “cute,” right?

Sometimes I feel overwhelmed and defeated… BUT then I take a step back, I look around, and I say to myself, “I F*ING BUILT THIS.” 👇

Zooming out is a skill I am constantly working on. As a hyperrealist painter, I tend to focus in on every detail — every inch — as if it were the entire painting. But then I also need to zoom out and focus on the painting as a whole. If I get lost in the details, the painting just won’t work. I need to adopt a micro AND macro perspective… simple, right? 🤪

I face the same sort of thing in business, when my workload seems larger than me… but then I remember to take a bird’s eye view. I MADE THIS. I made it through tons of overwhelm and elation and exhaustion and uncertainty… I felt all the feelings and I DID IT ANYWAY.

Every single time I heard the word NO… every look of disapproval or doubt when I said I was going to make it as a FT artist… every time I cried because I was the one disapproving or doubting… it all went into THIS. This beautiful thing I built. I want to honour every single building block.

Do you ever take a minute to ZOOM OUT and REALLY LOOK at what you’ve built — whether it’s a business or a family or a beautiful friendship… a painting, or even just tonight’s dinner… take a minute and say (preferably out loud) “I F*ING BUILT THIS.”

THE TOAST RETURNS… SORT OF👇

My toast print has been sold out in all four sizes for some time now, and I have never been asked MORE about the re-release of ANY print. As a rule, I do not re-release prints because they are all limited edition, signed and numbered. BUT…

I have been sitting on a small reserve of Artist Proofs from my own personal collection, which I have finally decided to sell. DM for pricing. 

I can hear many of you thinking, “what are Artist Proofs?” Artist Proofs are exactly the same as other limited edition prints in terms of their aesthetic and overall quality, BUT they are part of a much smaller and more exclusive collection (frequently the property of the artist), and as such, they are often considered to be more valuable.

I have never released Artist Proofs, but demand for the Toast has been so completely overwhelming, and it would bring me so much joy to finally release my own personal collection. Besides, I think these pieces have grown tired of my company. Since there are only 10 in each size, I DO THINK these will go quickly. I suggest being on my website a little early, and refreshing it close to 8pm EST. Other tips and tricks include using Apple Pay, or anything that facilitates a speedy checkout. Vulnerable post 🤍 I was lying awake last night thinking about how my art has evolved. I guess the full truth is that I was lying awake scrutinizing the art I’ve been making, wondering if it’s “good enough.” I wondered how my Professors in art school would characterize the seriousness of my work — is it groundbreaking? Is it disruptive? Is it even making a dent… or am I just painting toast.

Can art be both disruptive AND delightful? I think it CAN. Because I think when we bring less NOISE to our work, we make space for others to bring their own ideas, feelings, dreams and desires. In that way, the art can be a sort of magnet for human connectedness. So something as “silly” or “joyful” as a piece of toast or a pair of flip flops can actually unlock parts of humanity that are decisively UNSILLY. And that’s exactly what I told my art professor at 3am when we had this imaginary conversation.

There is a lot of pressure on artists to make “important” work — to NEVER “sell out.” I think about this constantly. It’s funny, because “making it as an artist,” in the outside world, means commercial success. But from within the art world, “making it” often implies a sort of unawareness or even rejection of commercial success. So basically, there is a lot of pressure on artists, coming from all sorts of places, not to mention the pressure we put on ourselves… which brought me to my 3am imaginary rendezvous.

I rarely post about this. It’s a lot. It’s heavy — and I wanted to share that. Because even though I PROFOUNDLY believe that art can absolutely be light, and bright and joyful, and commercially viable, AND deeply impactful, and serious, and TRUE — all at once — I can’t be the only creative out there who’s up at 3am, thinking about all these things. Am I? Would love to hear your thoughts on this subject 👇let’s overthink this together.

VULNERABLE POST 🤍I often get asked: HOW do you find time for everything? Between art, the business of art, family time, personal time, friends, health & wellness 🤪 it’s A LOT. And I’m going to tell you exactly how I do it👇

When I started running my business, I said YES to absolutely everything and everyone. I did a lot of work for free. I was determined to be a successful working artist, and every dollar, deal, and contact COUNTED — “Will you come to my home and hang this for me, and also hang all my other art?” SURE! “Will you do this for free on the promise of exposure?” SURE! — I felt like I needed to chase down sales and bargain for results. And that worked for me… then.

Some years back, in the midst of the pandemic, I came up with the “FU” business model. I was going to stop focusing on the chase, and start focusing on CREATING — a sort of FU to pandering to the man. I was going to paint whatever the F I wanted, and whoever loved it would buy it. Whoever didn’t love it, would not. Simple. Clean. Easy. Organic. Guess what happened when I did that👇

My business exploded. People LOVED my FU vibe. And to be clear, I was still friendly. I still listened to other people’s ideas. I genuinely love my buyers and followers, and I’m always open to new projects. But I got better at saying a polite NO to the things that weren’t aligned with my goals/greater purpose. And when I did that, I unlocked all this newfound time and energy. And that is how I’ve been able to grow and create and connect, both personally and professionally.

Which brings me to my NEW painting, a big shiny ROCK ON hand. There is no ROCK ON without FU. I would never have been able to rock my dream life without saying🖕to everything extraneous along the way. And let’s face it: FU neeeeeds ROCK ON. A signal to stay positive and follow your instincts, when the answer should indeed be HELL YES.

That’s why these paintings are SO meaningful to me. They symbolize the guideposts for the most brilliant and powerful decisions you’ll ever make: FU, ROCK ON, PEACE, LOVE… channel these in the right way, and you’ll be indestructible.

A NEW drop, entitled "Am Yisrael Chai" featuring any and all artwork created in celebration of my Jewish roots. 100% of the proceeds will be donated to the emergency campaign of United Jewish Appeal. Artwork will be hand-signed and titled at the bottom, with the words "Am Yisrael Chai" (the people of Israel LIVE). While I typically give you more notice where new drops are concerned, I simply didn't want to wait. "Am Yisrael Chai" is live on my site: link in BIO.

On a personal note (and I speak on behalf of my entire team):

We are horrified and grief stricken by the unspeakable acts of terrorism we continue to witness, and we extend our thoughts and prayers to anyone who is suffering. Please use your VOICE, even when it's hard, and even when it's scary. Regardless of our political views, this is a time for us to tap into our HUMANITY. We stand against hate. We stand against terrorism. Am Yisrael Chai.

We thank you from, the bottom of our hearts, for your unyielding love & support.

A personal message, in case anyone else is feeling the same way:

I have been supremely preoccupied this week. I am exhausted, horrified & heartbroken in a way I never thought possible. Between thinking about the victims out there, thinking about how to protect my family, thinking about how to help and what to say here on social media... I'm wiped. I haven't been able to focus on work or self-care in any kind of meaningful way.

And that is OK. I could easily say I've been distracted from this and that, but the truth is, my regular routine feels like a distraction from THIS. THIS is the important stuff - leading with our humanity and showing up for one another in times of need. Everything else is icing on the cake. THIS is the cake.

That being said: if you're feeling anything like me right now, go easy on yourself. Forgive yourself. Love yourself. Feel your feelings. Meditate. Mourn. Take a walk. Breathe. Cry. Laugh. I promise, you're in good company. Life will be here when you're ready for it, and in the meantime, it's ok to say “I need a minute."

*And for anyone who hasn’t already made a purchase: my drop “Am Yisrael Chai” is on until 4pm ET tomorrow, Tuesday, Oct. 17th. 100% of the proceeds will be donated to the emergency campaign of UJA. Artwork will be hand-signed and titled at the bottom with the words “Am Yisrael Chai” (the people of Israel LIVE). A MASSIVE thank you to everyone who has already purchased. Your support is everything ❤️.

Yesterday, the buyer of the original painting came forward and asked if I could help sell it in order to donate the proceeds to the emergency campaign of The United Jewish Appeal. I was incredibly touched, and decided that my recent dumpling painting could take a back seat.

Amidst my usual drops, which I believe bring light and love to people's hearts and homes, I speak for my entire team when I say that we ALSO want to do whatever we can to help those who are suffering right now. While I typically give you more notice where new artwork is concerned, I simply didn't want to wait.

I am SO grateful for the support of this incredible art-loving community, and I want to emphasize that there is more work to be done, where ALL innocent civilians are concerned. Regardless of our political views, this is a time for us to tap into our HUMANITY. We stand against hate, and we stand against terrorism. We lead with our heARTs.

We thank you, truly, for your unyielding love & support.
